}
</code></pre> <p>NOTE: If this is the only site you are hosting on this server (it should be :)) then you will need to disable the default site.</p> <p>Delete the <code>server</code> section from <code>/etc/nginx/nginx.conf</code></p> <pre><code>systemctl enable --now nginx
systemctl enable --now php-fpm
</code></pre> <p>Create the librenms.conf:</p> <pre><code>vi /etc/httpd/conf.d/librenms.conf
</code></pre> <p>Add the following config, edit <code>ServerName</code> as required:</p> <pre><code>&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;
  DocumentRoot /opt/librenms/html/
  ServerName  librenms.example.com

  AllowEncodedSlashes NoDecode
  &lt;Directory "/opt/librenms/html/"&gt;
    Require all granted
    AllowOverride All
    Options FollowSymLinks MultiViews
  &lt;/Directory&gt;

  # Enable http authorization headers
  &lt;IfModule setenvif_module&gt;
    SetEnvIfNoCase ^Authorization$ "(.+)" HTTP_AUTHORIZATION=$1
  &lt;/IfModule&gt;

  &lt;FilesMatch ".+\.php$"&gt;
    SetHandler "proxy:unix:/run/php-fpm-librenms.sock|fcgi://localhost"
  &lt;/FilesMatch&gt;
&lt;/VirtualHost&gt;
</code></pre> <p>NOTE: If this is the only site you are hosting on this server (it should be :)) then you will need to disable the default site. <code>rm -f /etc/httpd/conf.d/welcome.conf</code></p> <pre><code>systemctl enable --now httpd
systemctl enable --now php-fpm
</code></pre> NGINX <pre><code>vi /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/librenms.vhost
</code></pre> <p>Add the following config, edit <code>server_name</code> as required:</p> <pre><code>server {
